nglish/prejudice_2\">prejudice</a></div></div>\n","matches":["prejudice noun","Pride and Prejudice","without prejudice (to something)"],"relatives":["prejudice noun","Pride and Prejudice","without prejudice (to something)","without prejudice (to something)"],"nearBys":["prejudge verb","prejudice noun","prejudice verb","prejudiced adjective","prejudicial adjective"]},{"name":"Pride and Prejudice","pos":"adjective","content":"<div class=\"entry\" sum=\"726\" hclass=\"entry\" hlength=\"19\" id=\"pride-and-prejudice\" htag=\"section\" sk=\"prideandprejudice: :10\" idm_id=\"000046686\"><div class=\"top-container\"><div class=\"top-g\" id=\"pride_and_prejudice_topg_1\"><div class=\"webtop\"><h1 class=\"headword\" hclass=\"headword\" id=\"pride_and_prejudice_h_1\" title=\"y\" htag=\"h1\">Pride and Prejudice</h1> <span class=\"phonetics\"> <div class=\"phons_br\" geo=\"br\" htag=\"div\" hclass=\"phons_br\" wd=\"Pride and Prejudice\"><div class=\"sound audio_play_button pron-uk icon-audio\" data-src-mp3=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/media/english/uk_pron/p/pri/pride/pride_and_prejudice_1_gb_1.mp3\" data-src-ogg=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/media/english/uk_pron_ogg/p/pri/pride/pride_and_prejudice_1_gb_1.ogg\" title=\"Pride and Prejudice pronunciation\n                    English\" style=\"cursor: pointer\" valign=\"top\">&nbsp;</div><span class=\"phon\">/ˌpraɪd ən ˈpredʒədɪs/</span></div> <div class=\"phons_n_am\" hclass=\"phons_n_am\" wd=\"Pride and Prejudice\" geo=\"n_am\" htag=\"div\"><div class=\"sound audio_play_button pron-us icon-audio\" data-src-mp3=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/media/english/us_pron/p/pri/pride/pride_and_prejudice_1_us_1.mp3\" data-src-ogg=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/media/english/us_pron_ogg/p/pri/pride/pride_and_prejudice_1_us_1.ogg\" title=\"Pride and Prejudice pronunciation\n                    American\" style=\"cursor: pointer\" valign=\"top\">&nbsp;</div><span class=\"phon\">/ˌpraɪd ən ˈpredʒədɪs/</span></div></span></div><a class=\"responsive_display_inline_on_smartphone link-right\" href=\"#relatedentries\">\n                            jump to other results\n                        </a></div></div><ol class=\"sense_single\" htag=\"ol\"><li class=\"sense\" id=\"prideandprejudice_sng_1\" htag=\"li\" hclass=\"sense\"><a class=\"open oup_icons\" title=\"Add to My Word Lists\"><span class=\"star-btn\" aria-hidden=\"true\">​</span></a><span class=\"sensetop\" htag=\"span\" hclass=\"sensetop\"><span class=\"def\" htag=\"span\" hclass=\"def\">a novel (1813) by <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/jane-austen\" title=\"Jane Austen definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">Jane Austen</span></a>. Its main characters are the sensible and intelligent Elizabeth Bennet and the rich and <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/handsome#handsome_sng_1\" title=\"handsome definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">handsome</span></a> Fitzwilliam Darcy. Elizabeth at first dislikes Darcy because of his pride, but they finally recognize each other's good qualities and fall in love. The book ends with their marriage and that of another couple, Elizabeth's sister Jane and Darcy's friend Charles Bingley. It is one of Austen's most popular books and has been filmed several times.<span class=\"blockquote\"><span class=\"p-g\"><span class=\"wrap_open\">“</span><span class=\"p\">It is a truth universally acknowledged, that a single man in possession of a good fortune, must be in want of a wife.</span><span class=\"wrap_close\">”</span></span><span class=\"footer\">the beginning of <span class=\"ei\">Pride and Prejudice</span></span></span></span></span>    \n</li></ol><div class=\"pron-link\">Check pronunciation:\n                        <a href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/pronunciation/english/pride-and-prejudice\">Pride and Prejudice</a></div></div>\n","matches":[],"relatives":[],"nearBys":["pride noun","pride verb","Pride and Prejudice","pride yourself on phrasal verb","priest noun"]}]]